<section xml:id="s_chromatic_index">
<title>Chromatic index</title>


<definition><title>Chromatic index</title>
<p>The <em>chromatic number</em> <m>\chi^\prime(G)</m> of a graph G is the least number of colours needed to colour the edges of G so that edges that share a vertex have different colours.
</p></definition>


</section>